public class Greet {
    public static void main( String[] args ) {
	System.out.println("Hello, world!");
    }
}

/*
Similarities to Python/Scheme
- There's a print statement contained inside a function
- There are methods
- The function takes an argument

Differences to Python/Scheme
- There's a class in which the function resides in
- Semicolons indicate the end of a line
- Curly brackets indicate functions or classes
- Println is a method
*/
